      "question": "In $\\triangle ABC$, $\\angle ABC = 90^\\circ$. A point $D$ lies on $AC$ such that $BD \\perp AC$. If $AD = 4 \\text{ cm}$ and $DC = 9 \\text{ cm}$, find the length of $BD$.",
      "answer": "$6 \\text{ cm}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify that in a right-angled triangle, a perpendicular drawn from the right-angle vertex to the hypotenuse divides the triangle into two triangles that are similar to the original triangle and to each other.",
          "By similarity, $\\triangle ADB \\sim \\triangle BDC$.",
          "Using the property of similar triangles, the ratio of corresponding sides is equal, so $\\frac{AD}{BD} = \\frac{BD}{DC}$.",
          "Substitute the given values $AD = 4$ and $DC = 9$ into the equation $BD^2 = AD \\times DC$ and solve for $BD$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$In \\ \\triangle ADB \\ and \\ \\triangle BDC, \\ \\angle A + \\angle ABD = 90^\\circ \\ and \\ \\angle C + \\angle CBD = 90^\\circ \\\\ Since \\ \\angle ABD + \\angle CBD = 90^\\circ, \\ we \\ have \\ \\angle A = \\angle CBD \\ and \\ \\angle C = \\angle ABD \\\\ \\triangle ADB \\sim \\triangle BDC \\ (by \\ AA \\ similarity) \\\\ \\frac{AD}{BD} = \\frac{BD}{DC} \\\\ BD^2 = 4 \\times 9 \\\\ BD^2 = 36 \\\\ BD = \\sqrt{36} = 6 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
